<div class="feature-list-group">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row header">
      <h3>What is Mesos? A distributed systems kernel</h3>
      <p class="lead">
        Mesos is built using the same principles as the Linux kernel, only
        at a different level of abstraction. The Mesos<br>kernel runs on
        every machine and provides applications (e.g., Hadoop, Spark, Kafka,
        Elastic Search) with API’s for<br>resource management and scheduling
        across entire datacenter and cloud environments.
      </p>
    </div><!-- /.header -->

    <div class="row feature-list">
      <div class="col-md-3 col-sm-3 feature-item">
        <h4>Liner scalability</h4>
        <p >Industry proven to easily scale to 10,000s of nodes.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="col-md-3 col-sm-3 feature-item">
        <h4>Zookeeper</h4>
        <p>Fault-tolerant replicated master and agents using Zookeeper.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="col-md-3 col-sm-3 feature-item">
        <h4>Docker containers</h4>
        <p>Support for launching tasks that contains Docker iamges, with
        aslo a subset of Docker options.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="col-md-3 col-sm-3 feature-item">
        <h4>Linux containers</h4>
        <p>Native isolation between tasks with Linux Containers.</p>
      </div>
    </div><!-- /.feature-list -->

    <div class="row feature-list">
      <div class="col-md-3 col-sm-3 feature-item">
        <h4>Resource scheduling</h4>
        <p>Mesos provides a mechanism for operators scheduling (memory, CPU,
        disk, and ports).</p>
      </div>

      <div class="col-md-3 col-sm-3 feature-item">
        <h4>API</h4>
        <p>Java, Python and C++ APIs for developing new parallel
        applications.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="col-md-3 col-sm-3 feature-item">
        <h4>Web UI</h4>
        <p>Built in Web UI for viewing cluster state.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="col-md-3 col-sm-3 feature-item">
        <h4>Easy to use</h4>
        <p>See <a href="/gettingstarted/">getting started</a> section and give
        it a try.</p>
      </div>
    </div><!-- /.feature-list -->

